<h1 class="title">GRACE International Meeting on Bidirectional Transformations</h1>
<h2 class="title">(GRACE-BX 2008)</h2>
<h2 class="title"><a href="http://www.shonan-village.co.jp/english_index.html">
Shonan Village Center</a>, Japan, December 15&ndash;18, 2008</h2>
</div>

<div class="block">
  <h2 class="header">News</h2>
  <ul>
	<li>July 21: This page is opened.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="block">
  <h2 class="header">OBJECTIVE</h2>
<p>
Bidirectional transformations are a novel mechanism for synchronizing
and maintaining the consistency of information between input and
output. Recently, researchers from many different areas of computing
including programming languages, software engineering, databases,
document engineering, etc. have proposed bidirectional transformations
as solutions to a diverse set of problems.  The purpose of this GRACE
international meeting is to build on this growing interest in
bidirectional transformations, and bring together the international
elites, promising young researchers, and leading practitioners to
share problems and solutions, and to open a dialogue towards
understanding the common underpinnings of bidirectional
  transformations.
</p>

<p>
  Particular topics of interest include:
</p>
<ul id="topics_of_interest">
  <li>Programming Languages:
	<ul>
	  <li> Foundations of Bidirectional Computation</li>
	  <li> Bidirectional Programming Languages</li>
	  <li> Automatic Bidirectionalization</li>
	  <li> Inverse Computation</li>
	  <li> Invertible Programming</li>
	</ul>
  </li>
  <li>Software Engineering:
	<ul>
	  <li>Bidirectional Model Transformation</li>
	  <li>Software Artifact Synchronization</li>
	  <li>Software Maintenance and Evolution</li>
	  <li>Consistency management</li>
	  <li>Reverse Engineering</li>
	</ul>
  </li>
  <li>Database:
	<ul>
	  <li>Semantics of View Update</li>
	  <li>View Update Checking</li>
	  <li>Schema Mappings</li>
	  <li>Data Integration and Exchange</li>
	  <li>Data Synchronization</li>
	</ul>
  </li>
  <li>Others:
	<ul>
	  <li>Synchronization among intelligent agents</li>
	  <li>System Configuration Management</li>
	  <li>Graphical User Interface</li>
	  <li>Presentation-oriented Document Construction</li>
	</ul>
  </li>
</ul>

</div>

<div class="block">
<h2 class="header">ABOUT THE GRACE INTERNATIONAL MEETINGS</h2>
<p>
The GRACE International Meetings in Japan follow the style of the
successful <a href="http://www.dagstuhl.de/en/program/dagstuhl-seminars/">Dagstuhl Seminars</a>.
</p>

<p>
There is no set program followed at the meeting. The pace and the
procedure followed are determined by the short presentations offered
during the meeting and the discussion results.
</p>

<p>
The meeting is sponsored by the <a href="http://grace-center.jp/en/index.html">
GRACE International Center on Advanced
Software Science and Engineering</a> of <a href="http://www.nii.ac.jp/index.shtml.en">
National Institute of Informatics</a>
(NII) in Japan.
</p>
</div>

